\begin_layout Subsection*
2.1.
 Basics 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*
2.1.1.Image tab Load image
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Click on the tab 
\begin_inset Formula $Image$
\end_inset

 , then the button 
\begin_inset Formula $Load$
\end_inset

 , then choose any image from your computer.
 The result will be shown in the first axes window 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*
2.1.2.
 Load video
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Click on the button 
\begin_inset Formula $Browse$
\end_inset

 , to get the file path of the video you wan to watch .
 Then click on 
\begin_inset Formula $Start$
\end_inset

 to start the video.
 The video can be observed in the top window
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*
2.1.3.
 Save Image
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The button 
\begin_inset Formula $Save$
\end_inset

 is used to save any output image anywhere in the desktop.
 
\end_layout

