\begin_layout Subsection*
2.7.
 Edge detection 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Edge detection is a fundamental tool in image processing, machine vision
 and computer vision, particularly in the areas of feature detection and
 feature extraction.
 In the ideal case, the result of applying an edge detector to an image
 may lead to a set of connected curves that indicate the boundaries of objects,
 the boundaries of surface.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
To apply the edge detector operators on the image you must specify 
\begin_inset Formula $rgb2gray$
\end_inset

 as colorspace then inside the 
\begin_inset Formula $Edge\,detection$
\end_inset

 box , click on the arrow then choose the operator you want to apply to
 the inage between 
\begin_inset Formula $Sobel$
\end_inset

.
 
\begin_inset Formula $Prewitt$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $Roberts$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $Canny$
\end_inset

.
 The results are shown in the figure 8.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Figure 8: Sobel, Prewitt , Roberts, Canny (left to right)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
